[[File:Frantisek Bublan in 2012.JPG|thumb|František Bublan in 2012.]]
'''František Bublan''' (born 13 January 1951 in [[Třebíč]]) is a former [[Czech people|Czech]] [[dissident]], in 2004 named [[Minister of the Interior]] for [[Stanislav Gross]]'s [[Czech Social Democratic Party|Social Democratic Party]] government.<ref name="defence"/> After Stanislav Gross had been forced to leave the government, Bublan remained in the [[Jiří Paroubek's Cabinet|government of Jiří Paroubek]].

He studied at [[Charles University]], faculty of [[theology|Catholic Theology]].<ref name="defence">{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceandstrategy.eu/cs/autori/mgr-frantisek-bublan.html|title=Mgr. František Bublan|publisher=Defence and Strategy|language=Czech|accessdate=27 February 2010}}</ref> He briefly worked as cleric, but after signing [[Charter 77]], he had to work in menial jobs.<ref name="defence"/>

